snippets.title: VmwareEngine listPrivateClouds Sample
snippets.description: Lists `PrivateCloud` resources in a given project and location.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getPrivateCloud Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `PrivateCloud` resource by its resource name.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createPrivateCloud Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new `PrivateCloud` resource in a given project and location. Private clouds of type `STANDARD` and `TIME_LIMITED` are zonal resources, `STRETCHED` private clouds are regional. Creating a private cloud also creates a [management cluster](https://cloud.google.com/vmware-engine/docs/concepts-vmware-components) for that private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updatePrivateCloud Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a `PrivateCloud` resource. Only the following fields can be updated: `description`. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied. During operation processing, the resource is temporarily in the `ACTIVE` state before the operation fully completes. For that period of time, you can't update the resource. Use the operation status to determine when the processing fully completes.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deletePrivateCloud Sample
snippets.description: Schedules a `PrivateCloud` resource for deletion. A `PrivateCloud` resource scheduled for deletion has `PrivateCloud.state` set to `DELETED` and `expireTime` set to the time when deletion is final and can no longer be reversed. The delete operation is marked as done as soon as the `PrivateCloud` is successfully scheduled for deletion (this also applies when `delayHours` is set to zero), and the operation is not kept in pending state until `PrivateCloud` is purged. `PrivateCloud` can be restored using `UndeletePrivateCloud` method before the `expireTime` elapses. When `expireTime` is reached, deletion is final and all private cloud resources are irreversibly removed and billing stops. During the final removal process, `PrivateCloud.state` is set to `PURGING`. `PrivateCloud` can be polled using standard `GET` method for the whole period of deletion and purging. It will not be returned only when it is completely purged.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine undeletePrivateCloud Sample
snippets.description: Restores a private cloud that was previously scheduled for deletion by `DeletePrivateCloud`. A `PrivateCloud` resource scheduled for deletion has `PrivateCloud.state` set to `DELETED` and `PrivateCloud.expireTime` set to the time when deletion can no longer be reversed.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listClusters Sample
snippets.description: Lists `Cluster` resources in a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getCluster Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `Cluster` resource by its resource name.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new cluster in a given private cloud. Creating a new cluster provides additional nodes for use in the parent private cloud and requires sufficient [node quota](https://cloud.google.com/vmware-engine/quotas).

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a `Cluster` resource. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied. During operation processing, the resource is temporarily in the `ACTIVE` state before the operation fully completes. For that period of time, you can't update the resource. Use the operation status to determine when the processing fully completes.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `Cluster` resource. To avoid unintended data loss, migrate or gracefully shut down any workloads running on the cluster before deletion. You cannot delete the management cluster of a private cloud using this method.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listNodes Sample
snippets.description: Lists nodes in a given cluster.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getNode Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single node.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listExternalAddresses Sample
snippets.description: Lists external IP addresses assigned to VMware workload VMs in a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine fetchNetworkPolicyExternalAddresses Sample
snippets.description: Lists external IP addresses assigned to VMware workload VMs within the scope of the given network policy.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getExternalAddress Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single external IP address.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createExternalAddress Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new `ExternalAddress` resource in a given private cloud. The network policy that corresponds to the private cloud must have the external IP address network service enabled (`NetworkPolicy.external_ip`).

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateExternalAddress Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of a single external IP address. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied. During operation processing, the resource is temporarily in the `ACTIVE` state before the operation fully completes. For that period of time, you can't update the resource. Use the operation status to determine when the processing fully completes.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteExternalAddress Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a single external IP address. When you delete an external IP address, connectivity between the external IP address and the corresponding internal IP address is lost.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listSubnets Sample
snippets.description: Lists subnets in a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getSubnet Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single subnet.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateSubnet Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of a single subnet. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied. *Note*: This API is synchronous and always returns a successful `google.longrunning.Operation` (LRO). The returned LRO will only have `done` and `response` fields.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listExternalAccessRules Sample
snippets.description: Lists `ExternalAccessRule` resources in the specified network policy.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getExternalAccessRule Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single external access rule.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createExternalAccessRule Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new external access rule in a given network policy.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateExternalAccessRule Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of a single external access rule. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteExternalAccessRule Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a single external access rule.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listLoggingServers Sample
snippets.description: Lists logging servers configured for a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getLoggingServer Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a logging server.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createLoggingServer Sample
snippets.description: Create a new logging server for a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateLoggingServer Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of a single logging server. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteLoggingServer Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a single logging server.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listNodeTypes Sample
snippets.description: Lists node types

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getNodeType Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of a single `NodeType`.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine showNsxCredentials Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of credentials for NSX appliance.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine showVcenterCredentials Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of credentials for Vcenter appliance.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine resetNsxCredentials Sample
snippets.description: Resets credentials of the NSX appliance.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine resetVcenterCredentials Sample
snippets.description: Resets credentials of the Vcenter appliance.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getDnsForwarding Sample
snippets.description: Gets details of the `DnsForwarding` config.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateDnsForwarding Sample
snippets.description: Updates the parameters of the `DnsForwarding` config, like associated domains. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getNetworkPeering Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `NetworkPeering` resource by its resource name. The resource contains details of the network peering, such as peered networks, import and export custom route configurations, and peering state. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listNetworkPeerings Sample
snippets.description: Lists `NetworkPeering` resources in a given project. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createNetworkPeering Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new network peering between the peer network and VMware Engine network provided in a `NetworkPeering` resource. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteNetworkPeering Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `NetworkPeering` resource. When a network peering is deleted for a VMware Engine network, the peer network becomes inaccessible to that VMware Engine network. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateNetworkPeering Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a `NetworkPeering` resource. Only the `description` field can be updated. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listPeeringRoutes Sample
snippets.description: Lists the network peering routes exchanged over a peering connection. NetworkPeering is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createHcxActivationKey Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new HCX activation key in a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listHcxActivationKeys Sample
snippets.description: Lists `HcxActivationKey` resources in a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getHcxActivationKey Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `HcxActivationKey` resource by its resource name.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getNetworkPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `NetworkPolicy` resource by its resource name.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listNetworkPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Lists `NetworkPolicy` resources in a specified project and location.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createNetworkPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new network policy in a given VMware Engine network of a project and location (region). A new network policy cannot be created if another network policy already exists in the same scope.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateNetworkPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a `NetworkPolicy` resource. Only the following fields can be updated: `internet_access`, `external_ip`, `edge_services_cidr`. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied. When updating a network policy, the external IP network service can only be disabled if there are no external IP addresses present in the scope of the policy. Also, a `NetworkService` cannot be updated when `NetworkService.state` is set to `RECONCILING`. During operation processing, the resource is temporarily in the `ACTIVE` state before the operation fully completes. For that period of time, you can't update the resource. Use the operation status to determine when the processing fully completes.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteNetworkPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `NetworkPolicy` resource. A network policy cannot be deleted when `NetworkService.state` is set to `RECONCILING` for either its external IP or internet access service.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listManagementDnsZoneBindings Sample
snippets.description: Lists Consumer VPCs bound to Management DNS Zone of a given private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getManagementDnsZoneBinding Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a 'ManagementDnsZoneBinding' resource by its resource name.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createManagementDnsZoneBinding Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new `ManagementDnsZoneBinding` resource in a private cloud. This RPC creates the DNS binding and the resource that represents the DNS binding of the consumer VPC network to the management DNS zone. A management DNS zone is the Cloud DNS cross-project binding zone that VMware Engine creates for each private cloud. It contains FQDNs and corresponding IP addresses for the private cloud's ESXi hosts and management VM appliances like vCenter and NSX Manager.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateManagementDnsZoneBinding Sample
snippets.description: Updates a `ManagementDnsZoneBinding` resource. Only fields specified in `update_mask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteManagementDnsZoneBinding Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `ManagementDnsZoneBinding` resource. When a management DNS zone binding is deleted, the corresponding consumer VPC network is no longer bound to the management DNS zone.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine repairManagementDnsZoneBinding Sample
snippets.description: Retries to create a `ManagementDnsZoneBinding` resource that is in failed state.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createVmwareEngineNetwork Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new VMware Engine network that can be used by a private cloud.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updateVmwareEngineNetwork Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a VMware Engine network resource. Only the following fields can be updated: `description`. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deleteVmwareEngineNetwork Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `VmwareEngineNetwork` resource. You can only delete a VMware Engine network after all resources that refer to it are deleted. For example, a private cloud, a network peering, and a network policy can all refer to the same VMware Engine network.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getVmwareEngineNetwork Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `VmwareEngineNetwork` resource by its resource name. The resource contains details of the VMware Engine network, such as its VMware Engine network type, peered networks in a service project, and state (for example, `CREATING`, `ACTIVE`, `DELETING`).

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listVmwareEngineNetworks Sample
snippets.description: Lists `VmwareEngineNetwork` resources in a given project and location.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine createPrivateConnection Sample
snippets.description: Creates a new private connection that can be used for accessing private Clouds.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getPrivateConnection Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves a `PrivateConnection` resource by its resource name. The resource contains details of the private connection, such as connected network, routing mode and state.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listPrivateConnections Sample
snippets.description: Lists `PrivateConnection` resources in a given project and location.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine updatePrivateConnection Sample
snippets.description: Modifies a `PrivateConnection` resource. Only `description` and `routing_mode` fields can be updated. Only fields specified in `updateMask` are applied.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine deletePrivateConnection Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a `PrivateConnection` resource. When a private connection is deleted for a VMware Engine network, the connected network becomes inaccessible to that VMware Engine network.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine listPrivateConnectionPeeringRoutes Sample
snippets.description: Lists the private connection routes exchanged over a peering connection.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine grantDnsBindPermission Sample
snippets.description: Grants the bind permission to the customer provided principal(user / service account) to bind their DNS zone with the intranet VPC associated with the project. DnsBindPermission is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine getDnsBindPermission Sample
snippets.description: Gets all the principals having bind permission on the intranet VPC associated with the consumer project granted by the Grant API. DnsBindPermission is a global resource and location can only be global.

snippets.title: VmwareEngine revokeDnsBindPermission Sample
snippets.description: Revokes the bind permission from the customer provided principal(user / service account) on the intranet VPC associated with the consumer project. DnsBindPermission is a global resource and location can only be global.
